# Fixtures and golden transcripts are byte-exact. Git must never normalize line
# endings, strip trailing whitespace, or run text diffs/merges on these paths.
# The transcripts pin TestSuite's real output, whose report lines DELIBERATELY
# carry trailing spaces, and whose exact bytes are regenerated and diffed
# byte-for-byte by the CI gate — a "helpful" CRLF->LF rewrite or whitespace
# strip would silently invalidate every golden. The `**` recursive form is
# required: a bare `fixtures/ -text` directory pattern does NOT apply to the
# files inside it.
fixtures/**       -text
goldens/**        -text

# The pixi lock is machine-generated; treat it as binary so a stale local diff
# never triggers a 3-way merge, and keep GitHub from counting it as source.
pixi.lock merge=binary linguist-language=YAML linguist-generated=true -diff
